  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Placement of a vaginal pessary reduces significantly the rate of spontaneous preterm birth in
      pregnant women with short cervical length after an episode of threatened preterm labour.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Completed</overall_status>
